  22 def pid_exists(pid):
  23     """Check whether pid exists in the current process table."""
  24     if pid == 0:
  25         # According to "man 2 kill" PID 0 has a special meaning:
  26         # it refers to <<every process in the process group of the
  27         # calling process>> so we don't want to go any further.
  28         # If we get here it means this UNIX platform *does* have
  29         # a process with id 0.
  30         return True
  31     try:
  32         os.kill(pid, 0)
  33     except OSError as err:
  34         if err.errno == errno.ESRCH:
  35             # ESRCH == No such process
  36             return False
  37         elif err.errno == errno.EPERM:
  38             # EPERM clearly means there's a process to deny access to
  39             return True
  40         else:
  41             # According to "man 2 kill" possible error values are
  42             # (EINVAL, EPERM, ESRCH) therefore we should never get
  43             # here. If we do let's be explicit in considering this
  44             # an error.
  45             raise err
  46     else:
  47         return True

  50 class Command(object):
  51     def __init__(self, cmd, timeout=TIMEOUT):
  52         super(Command, self).__init__()
  53         self.cmd = cmd
  54         self.timeout = timeout
  55         self.subprocess = None
  56         self.blocking = None
  57         self.was_run = False
  58         self.__out = None
  59         self.__err = None
  60 
  61     def __repr__(self):
  62         return "<Command {!r}>".format(self.cmd)
  63 
  64     @property
  65     def _popen_args(self):
  66         return self.cmd
  67 
  68     @property
  69     def _default_popen_kwargs(self):
  70         return {
  71             "env": os.environ.copy(),
  72             "stdin": subprocess.PIPE,
  73             "stdout": subprocess.PIPE,
  74             "stderr": subprocess.PIPE,
  75             "shell": True,
  76             "universal_newlines": True,
  77             "bufsize": 0,
  78         }
  79 
  80     @property
  81     def _default_pexpect_kwargs(self):
  82         encoding = "utf-8"
  83         if sys.platform == "win32":
  84             default_encoding = locale.getdefaultlocale()[1]
  85             if default_encoding is not None:
  86                 encoding = default_encoding
  87         return {"env": os.environ.copy(), "encoding": encoding, "timeout": self.timeout}
  88 
  89     @property
  90     def _uses_subprocess(self):
  91         return isinstance(self.subprocess, subprocess.Popen)
  92 
  93     @property
  94     def _uses_pexpect(self):
  95         return isinstance(self.subprocess, PopenSpawn)
  96 
  97     @property
  98     def std_out(self):
  99         return self.subprocess.stdout
 100 
 101     @property
 102     def ok(self):
 103         return self.return_code == 0
 104 
 105     @property
 106     def _pexpect_out(self):
 107         if self.subprocess.encoding:
 108             result = ""
 109         else:
 110             result = b""
 111 
 112         if self.subprocess.before:
 113             result += self.subprocess.before
 114 
 115         if self.subprocess.after and self.subprocess.after not in (pexpect.EOF, pexpect.TIMEOUT):
 116             try:
 117                 result += self.subprocess.after
 118             except (pexpect.EOF, pexpect.TIMEOUT):
 119                 pass
 120 
 121         result += self.subprocess.read()
 122         return result
 123 
 124     @property
 125     def out(self):
 126         """Std/out output (cached)"""
 127         if self.__out is not None:
 128             return self.__out
 129 
 130         if self._uses_subprocess:
 131             self.__out = self.std_out.read()
 132         else:
 133             self.__out = self._pexpect_out
 134 
 135         return self.__out
 136 
 137     @property
 138     def std_err(self):
 139         return self.subprocess.stderr
 140 
 141     @property
 142     def err(self):
 143         """Std/err output (cached)"""
 144         if self.__err is not None:
 145             return self.__err
 146 
 147         if self._uses_subprocess:
 148             self.__err = self.std_err.read()
 149             return self.__err
 150         else:
 151             return self._pexpect_out
 152 
 153     @property
 154     def pid(self):
 155         """The process' PID."""
 156         # Support for pexpect's functionality.
 157         if hasattr(self.subprocess, "proc"):
 158             return self.subprocess.proc.pid
 159         # Standard subprocess method.
 160         return self.subprocess.pid
 161 
 162     @property
 163     def is_alive(self):
 164         """Is the process alive?"""
 165         return pid_exists(self.pid)
 166 
 167     @property
 168     def return_code(self):
 169         # Support for pexpect's functionality.
 170         if self._uses_pexpect:
 171             return self.subprocess.exitstatus
 172         # Standard subprocess method.
 173         return self.subprocess.returncode
 174 
 175     @property
 176     def std_in(self):
 177         return self.subprocess.stdin
 178 
 179     def run(self, block=True, binary=False, cwd=None, env=None):
 180         """Runs the given command, with or without pexpect functionality enabled."""
 181         self.blocking = block
 182 
 183         # Use subprocess.
 184         if self.blocking:
 185             popen_kwargs = self._default_popen_kwargs.copy()
 186             del popen_kwargs["stdin"]
 187             popen_kwargs["universal_newlines"] = not binary
 188             if cwd:
 189                 popen_kwargs["cwd"] = cwd
 190             if env:
 191                 popen_kwargs["env"].update(env)
 192             s = subprocess.Popen(self._popen_args, **popen_kwargs)
 193         # Otherwise, use pexpect.
 194         else:
 195             pexpect_kwargs = self._default_pexpect_kwargs.copy()
 196             if binary:
 197                 pexpect_kwargs["encoding"] = None
 198             if cwd:
 199                 pexpect_kwargs["cwd"] = cwd
 200             if env:
 201                 pexpect_kwargs["env"].update(env)
 202             # Enable Python subprocesses to work with expect functionality.
 203             pexpect_kwargs["env"]["PYTHONUNBUFFERED"] = "1"
 204             s = PopenSpawn(self._popen_args, **pexpect_kwargs)
 205         self.subprocess = s
 206         self.was_run = True
 207 
 208     def expect(self, pattern, timeout=-1):
 209         """Waits on the given pattern to appear in std_out"""
 210 
 211         if self.blocking:
 212             raise RuntimeError("expect can only be used on non-blocking commands.")
 213 
 214         try:
 215             self.subprocess.expect(pattern=pattern, timeout=timeout)
 216         except pexpect.EOF:
 217             pass
 218 
 219     def send(self, s, end=os.linesep, signal=False):
 220         """Sends the given string or signal to std_in."""
 221 
 222         if self.blocking:
 223             raise RuntimeError("send can only be used on non-blocking commands.")
 224 
 225         if not signal:
 226             if self._uses_subprocess:
 227                 return self.subprocess.communicate(s + end)
 228             else:
 229                 return self.subprocess.send(s + end)
 230         else:
 231             self.subprocess.send_signal(s)
 232 
 233     def terminate(self):
 234         self.subprocess.terminate()
 235 
 236     def kill(self):
 237         if self._uses_pexpect:
 238             self.subprocess.kill(signal.SIGINT)
 239         else:
 240             self.subprocess.send_signal(signal.SIGINT)
 241 
 242     def block(self):
 243         """Blocks until process is complete."""
 244         if self._uses_subprocess:
 245             # consume stdout and stderr
 246             if self.blocking:
 247                 try:
 248                     stdout, stderr = self.subprocess.communicate()
 249                     self.__out = stdout
 250                     self.__err = stderr
 251                 except ValueError:
 252                     pass  # Don't read from finished subprocesses.
 253             else:
 254                 self.subprocess.stdin.close()
 255                 self.std_out.close()
 256                 self.std_err.close()
 257                 self.subprocess.wait()
 258         else:
 259             self.subprocess.sendeof()
 260             try:
 261                 self.subprocess.wait()
 262             finally:
 263                 if self.subprocess.proc.stdout:
 264                     self.subprocess.proc.stdout.close()
 265 
 266     def pipe(self, command, timeout=None, cwd=None):
 267         """Runs the current command and passes its output to the next
 268         given process.
 269         """
 270         if not timeout:
 271             timeout = self.timeout
 272 
 273         if not self.was_run:
 274             self.run(block=False, cwd=cwd)
 275 
 276         data = self.out
 277 
 278         if timeout:
 279             c = Command(command, timeout)
 280         else:
 281             c = Command(command)
 282 
 283         c.run(block=False, cwd=cwd)
 284         if data:
 285             c.send(data)
 286         c.block()
 287         return c

 290 def _expand_args(command):
 291     """Parses command strings and returns a Popen-ready list."""
 292 
 293     # Prepare arguments.
 294     if isinstance(command, STR_TYPES):
 295         if sys.version_info[0] == 2:
 296             splitter = shlex.shlex(command.encode("utf-8"))
 297         elif sys.version_info[0] == 3:
 298             splitter = shlex.shlex(command)
 299         else:
 300             splitter = shlex.shlex(command.encode("utf-8"))
 301         splitter.whitespace = "|"
 302         splitter.whitespace_split = True
 303         command = []
 304 
 305         while True:
 306             token = splitter.get_token()
 307             if token:
 308                 command.append(token)
 309             else:
 310                 break
 311 
 312         command = list(map(shlex.split, command))
 313 
 314     return command
 315 
 316 
 317 def chain(command, timeout=TIMEOUT, cwd=None, env=None):
 318     commands = _expand_args(command)
 319     data = None
 320 
 321     for command in commands:
 322 
 323         c = run(command, block=False, timeout=timeout, cwd=cwd, env=env)
 324 
 325         if data:
 326             c.send(data)
 327             c.subprocess.sendeof()
 328 
 329         data = c.out
 330 
 331     return c
 332 
 333 
 334 def run(command, block=True, binary=False, timeout=TIMEOUT, cwd=None, env=None):
 335     c = Command(command, timeout=timeout)
 336     c.run(block=block, binary=binary, cwd=cwd, env=env)
 337 
 338     if block:
 339         c.block()
 340 
 341     return c
